cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces an epistemic logic for the applied pi calculus to express security properties. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as the paper deals with security properties and attackers. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses process algebras and equivalences between processes. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses verification of security properties. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with formalization of security properties.
